			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have five focus effects at level fifty nine (Mana Preservation, Affliction Efficiency, Burning Affliction, Spell Haste and Improved Damage) so my rundown may not be as complete as some of the others. Keep in mind these are only my opinions.
<br />

<br />
You want to get Affliction Efficiency above and beyond all else. It makes a huge difference that you will definitely notice especially when you get into the dots that are big mana burners (currently have a couple in the three fifty to four hundred range).
<br />

<br />
Burning Affliction is great though I would not list it as more important than Affliction Efficiency. You will definitely notice it helps but maybe not quite so much as you would notice improved damage with a wizard. 
<br />

<br />
Spell Haste is also a must in my opinion. You are going to have some slow ass casting spells. You are going to want to be able to get them off as quickly as possible. Especially your lifetaps which seem to take forever to cast until you get Deflux.
<br />

<br />
Mana Preservation is pretty take it or leave it. When you are soloing you are going to be using almost nothing but dots for damage so Affliction Efficiency will cover you and do so much better. I am glad I have it but would not pay for it if I did not (did the Kiki's Recipe quest for mine).
<br />

<br />
Improved Damage is another one that is not going to be all that game breaking for you but you can grab it if you want. You will notice a big improvement on your nukes but I rarely ever use them anyway unless I am grouping and fighting mobs with few hit points (mostly in Lost Dungeons of Norrath adventures). The extra heal on the lifetap is nice though.
<br />

<br />
All in all I would trade Spell haste, Mana Preservation and Improved Damage for Affliction Haste and Extended range if given the opportunity but would not give up Affliction Efficiency or Burning Affliction for anything.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
