			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you're soloing a lot, Extended Range is a must. If a snare fails, it will usually give you enough time to try twice more before the mob is on you.
<br />

<br />
If you solo more than group, I'd go for Extended Torment before Burning Affliction, but if you group a lot I'd get BA first since most battles probably won't last long enough for ET to make a difference.
<br />

<br />
Affliction Haste is very important when you have to lay a bunch of dots on a mob in a hurry when soloing and the haste it gives you beats Spell Haste.
<br />

<br />
BA, ET and ER are all available as augments from LDON if you find the bazaar items to be way overpriced. Why piss away 200K on Ceramic Shackles of Torment when you can buy an item with better stats and the BA IV augment by just grinding out a bunch of LDONs?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
